headline: Dr Pepper Goes Deep on Coffee With $18B JDE Peet's Deal
summary: Keurig Dr Pepper (KDP, Financials) is paying $18 billion to buy JDE Peet's, the Dutch coffee group behind brands like Douwe Egberts and L'Or  and it's not just a takeover, it's a reinvention.  Split the merged giant into two U.S.-listed companies: one focused entirely on coffee (Global Coffee Co), the other sticking to soda and beverages (Beverage Co).  Nestle  the world's coffee king  now has a new rival.

headline: The Stock Market Hates Keurig Dr Pepper’s Deal for Peet’s Coffee. Here’s Why.
summary: Keurig Dr Pepper  plans to acquire Dutch tea and coffee giant  JDE Peet  and then split into two public companies.  Keurig Dr Pepper stock plunged 11.5% on Monday after the $18 billion deal was announced, and another 5.6% on Tuesday.  The stock will likely stay under pressure in the near-to-intermediate term as the market wrestles with the surprising move, UBS analyst Peter Grom wrote in a Tuesday note.
